              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Kinematic elements toolbar &gt; Add Ball-Joint</text></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <list id="5" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#83;&#84;&#69;&#80;&#32;&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#58;&#32;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="false" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="HowTo STEP" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo STEP"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Ball-Joint #1</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">B</text> is active.<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></para>
                <list id="6" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-style:normal;">Click </text><text styleclass="Element" style="font-style:normal;">Point</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-style:normal;" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text style="font-style:normal;"> at the end of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> that is </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Completely-Free </text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:normal;">Click </text><text styleclass="Element" style="font-style:normal;">Point</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Body Text"> at the end of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> that is </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Free</text><text styleclass="Interface">.</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-weight:normal;">If you cannot select the two(2) </text><text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text style="font-weight:normal;"> to add a </text><text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text>, disable<text styleclass="Bullets"> the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Edit-AutoUpdate" styleclass="Bullets">Auto-Update tool</link><text styleclass="VariableName">, </text>and try again.</para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">After you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Ball-Joint #1</text> you can see the <text styleclass="VariableName">Ball-Joint symbol</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">However, <text styleclass="Element">Points</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">do not</text> snap together before you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Ball-Joint #2</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
